1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with cryptographic protocols and their analysis from a rational point of view. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses game-theoretical approach to model cryptographic protocols and possible misbehaviours of parties. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve concepts of information theory in the analysis of cryptographic protocols. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve complexity analysis of cryptographic protocols. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve algorithms and data structures used in cryptographic protocols.
